<li id="cite_note-Handbook_2010-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Handbook_2010_17-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171115192147/https://www.lds.org/manual/handbook-1-stake-presidents-and-bishops/ordinance-and-blessing-policies/ordinance-and-blessing-policies?lang=eng"><i>Handbook 1: Stake Presidents and Bishops</i></a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. 2010. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.lds.org/manual/handbook-1-stake-presidents-and-bishops/ordinance-and-blessing-policies/ordinance-and-blessing-policies?lang=eng">the original</a> on November 15, 2017 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>. <q>The mission president must conduct an interview and receive authorization from the First Presidency before a prospective convert may be baptized and confirmed if the person ... Has undergone an elective transsexual operation. ... A person who is considering an elective transsexual operation may not be baptized or confirmed. ... However, [persons who have already undergone an elective transsexual operation] may not receive the priesthood or a temple recommend.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Handbook+1%3A+Stake+Presidents+and+Bishops&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=2010&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lds.org%2Fmanual%2Fhandbook-1-stake-presidents-and-bishops%2Fordinance-and-blessing-policies%2Fordinance-and-blessing-policies%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class=