<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrown2015" class="citation news cs1">Brown, Jennifer (September 25, 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://extras.denverpost.com/transgender/alison.html">"Alison's Story"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Denver_Post" title="The Denver Post">The Denver Post</a></i>. <q>It was a crisis of faith that left Alison open to feel and to discover her identity. Half a year before she considered that she was transgender, Alison began questioning her belief in the Mormon Church. ... Alison now says that 'being trans and being in the church is like being in an abusive relationship.'<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Denver+Post&amp;rft.atitle=Alison%27s+Story&amp;rft.date=2015-09-25&amp;rft.aulast=Brown&amp;rft.aufirst=Jennifer&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fextras.denverpost.com%2Ftransgender%2Falison.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
