<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMusser1858" class="citation web cs1">Musser, Amos Milton (April 17, 1858). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://heritage.utah.gov/apps/history/findaids/B00096/B0096ff.xml#s1">"Papers of Amos Milton Musser: Private Journal"</a>. <i>heritage.utah.gov</i>. <a href="/wiki/Utah_State_Historical_Society" title="Utah State Historical Society">Utah State Historical Society</a>. <q>Almerin Grow has given me his daughter now twelve years old to raise. He has appointed me as her guardian guardian. Pres[ident] Young has given him a mission 'to go south and never return.' Though naturally smart, [Grow] has become immeasurably insane striking tokens of which are seen in his acts ... wearing his wife's clothing, etc.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=heritage.utah.gov&amp;rft.atitle=Papers+of+Amos+Milton+Musser%3A+Private+Journal&amp;rft.date=1858-04-17&amp;rft.aulast=Musser&amp;rft.aufirst=Amos+Milton&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fheritage.utah.gov%2Fapps%2Fhistory%2Ffindaids%2FB00096%2FB0096ff.xml%23s1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooks1961" class="citation thesis cs1">Brooks, Karl (1961). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171127000619/https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=5557&amp;context=etd"><i>The Life of Amos Milton Musser</i></a> (Master of Science thesis). <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a>. p.&#160;71. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://scholarsarchive.byu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=5557&amp;context=etd">the original</a> on November 27, 2017 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adissertation&amp;rft.title=The+Life+of+Amos+Milton+Musser&amp;rft.degree=Master+of+Science&amp;rft.inst=BYU&amp;rft.date=1961&amp;rft.aulast=Brooks&amp;rft.aufirst=Karl&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fscholarsarchive.byu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D5557%26context%3Detd&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith2007" class="citation thesis cs1">Smith, Daymon Mickel (2007). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.proquest.com/docview/304833179"><i>The last shall be first and the first shall be last: Discourse and Mormon history</i></a> (PhD). <a href="/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania" title="University of Pennsylvania">University of Pennsylvania</a>. p.&#160;77. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ProQuest_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ProQuest (identifier)">ProQuest</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://search.proquest.com/docview/304833179">304833179</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/ProQuest" title="ProQuest">ProQuest</a>. <q>[Wilford] Woodruff often hid in southern Utah, though his notoriety led to suspicions cast on anyone nearby. ... Seemingly benign requests for eggs or flour became, once Woodruff was around, indicators that the neighbors were potential spies. Yet [Emma] Squire does not report any action which verified this assumption; instead, Woodruff concealed himself in a 'mother hubbard' dress, and avoided anyone he did already trust.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Adissertation&amp;rft.title=The+last+shall+be+first+and+the+first+shall+be+last%3A+Discourse+and+Mormon+history&amp;rft.inst=University+of+Pennsylvania&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Daymon+Mickel&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proquest.com%2Fdocview%2F304833179&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.newspapers.com/clip/96438564/early-lds-prophet-goes-undercover-in/">"Early LDS prophet goes undercover in dress, sunbonnet"</a>. <i>The Spectrum</i>. St. George, UT. <a href="/wiki/Gannett" title="Gannett">Gannett</a>. July 12, 2006 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Newspapers.com" class="mw-redirect" title="Newspapers.com">Newspapers.com</a>. <q>Emma Squire made him a 'Mother Hubbard' dress and sunbonnet, similar to the ones she wore. He put them on when he went back and forth from the house so people passing could not recognize him. ... Years later, Emma met one of Woodruff's granddaughters and learned that they still had the 'Mother Hubbard' dress and bonnet in the family. They had often wondered who made them for him. They knew the items had been used for many years when he was in hiding.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Spectrum&amp;rft.atitle=Early+LDS+prophet+goes+undercover+in+dress%2C+sunbonnet&amp;rft.date=2006-07-12&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newspapers.com%2Fclip%2F96438564%2Fearly-lds-prophet-goes-undercover-in%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
