</li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBallard2002" class="citation magazine cs1"><a href="/wiki/M._Russell_Ballard" title="M. Russell Ballard">Ballard, M. Russell</a> (April 2002). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/ensign/2002/04/women-of-righteousness?lang=eng">"Women of Righteousness"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Ensign_(LDS_magazine)" title="Ensign (LDS magazine)">Ensign</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. pp.&#160;66–69. <q>The premortal and mortal natures of men and women were specified by God Himself. ...[Sometimes women] ask: 'Is a woman's value dependent exclusively upon her role as a wife and mother?' The answer is simple and obvious: No. ...Every righteous man and woman has a significant role to play in the onward march of the kingdom of God.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Ensign&amp;rft.atitle=Women+of+Righteousness&amp;rft.pages=66-69&amp;rft.date=2002-04&amp;rft.aulast=Ballard&amp;rft.aufirst=M.+Russell&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fensign%2F2002%2F04%2Fwomen-of-righteousness%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Harold-60"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Harold_60-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFWilliams1996" class="citation book cs1">Williams, Clyde J. (1996). <span class="id-lock-limited" title="Free access subject to limited trial, subscription normally required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=LXE3AAAACAAJ"><i>The Teachings of Harold B. Lee</i></a></span>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1570084836" title="Special:BookSources/978-1570084836"><bdi>978-1570084836</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Teachings+of+Harold+B.+Lee&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.isbn=978-1570084836&amp;rft.aulast=Williams&amp;rft.aufirst=Clyde+J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DLXE3AAAACAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
