<li id="cite_note-61"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-61">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFLee1970" class="citation speech cs1"><a href="/wiki/Harold_B._Lee" title="Harold B. Lee">Lee, Harold</a> (August 7, 1970). <span class="id-lock-subscription" title="Paid subscription required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.familysearch.org/library/books/records/item/588665-annual-priesthood-genealogical-research-seminar-provo-utah-1970-v-02?offset=2"><i>Fifth Annual Genealogical Seminar Address</i></a></span> (Speech). Fifth Annual Priesthood Genealogical Research Seminar. Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/FamilySearch" title="FamilySearch">FamilySearch</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Fifth+Annual+Genealogical+Seminar+Address&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=BYU&amp;rft.date=1970-08-07&amp;rft.aulast=Lee&amp;rft.aufirst=Harold&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.familysearch.org%2Flibrary%2Fbooks%2Frecords%2Fitem%2F588665-annual-priesthood-genealogical-research-seminar-provo-utah-1970-v-02%3Foffset%3D2&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-62"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-62">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation audio-visual cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://speeches.byu.edu/talks/spencer-w-kimball_ye-therefore-perfect/"><i>Be Ye Therefore Perfect</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. September 17, 1974.  Event occurs at 24:24 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/BYU" class="mw-redirect" title="BYU">BYU</a>. <q>[I]t is hard for me to understand why men wish to resemble women and why women desire to ape the men. ... Then we're appalled to find an ever-increasing number of women who want to be sexually men and many young men who wish to be sexually women. What a travesty! I tell you that, as surely as they live, such people will regret having made overtures toward the changing of their sex. Do they know better than God what is right and best for them?</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Be+Ye+Therefore+Perfect&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=1974-09-17&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fspeeches.byu.edu%2Ftalks%2Fspencer-w-kimball_ye-therefore-perfect%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span> Alternative <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u6Ng-RpcpbA&amp;t=24m24s">YouTube</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20180914110547/https://speeches.byu.edu/talks/spencer-w-kimball_ye-therefore-perfect/">Internet Archive</a> links.</span>
</li>
