<li id="cite_note-2016retired-72"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2016retired_72-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFletcher_Stack2016" class="citation news cs1"><a href="/wiki/Peggy_Fletcher_Stack" title="Peggy Fletcher Stack">Fletcher Stack, Peggy</a> (November 14, 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.sltrib.com/article.php?id=4584556&amp;itype=CMSID">"LDS Church 'retires' Mormon apostle's 'little factory' pamphlet"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Salt_Lake_Tribune" title="The Salt Lake Tribune">The Salt Lake Tribune</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 23,</span> 2023</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Salt+Lake+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=LDS+Church+%27retires%27+Mormon+apostle%27s+%27little+factory%27+pamphlet&amp;rft.date=2016-11-14&amp;rft.aulast=Fletcher+Stack&amp;rft.aufirst=Peggy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.sltrib.com%2Farticle.php%3Fid%3D4584556%26itype%3DCMSID&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-73"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-73">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPacker1978" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Boyd_K._Packer" title="Boyd K. Packer">Packer, Boyd K.</a> (1978). <i>To The One</i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. <q>[O]ne cannot increase masculinity or femininity by deviate physical contact with one of his own gender. ... When one projects [him or herself] in some confused role-playing way with those of the same gender in an effort to become more masculine or more feminine, something flips over and precisely the opposite results ... a female can become, in her emotions, less feminine and more masculine and confused ... because the body cannot change, the emotional part may struggle to transform itself into the opposite gender [sending the individual] on a hopeless, futile quest for identity where it can never be achieved.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=To+The+One&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft.aulast=Packer&amp;rft.aufirst=Boyd+K.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGender+minorities+and+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
